{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778377831400,"sessionID":"ses_1f06be284ffeWNxRiRPzllU5nl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7szu3HmYevopTE2o8Uhy7phA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"Following up on comments in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29539.\\n\\nThere are currently 5 nested GO terms for Entner-Doudoroff pathways, though only 1 has ever been used in annotation:\\n\\n```\\nEntner-Doudoroff pathway [0 direct annotations]\\n    |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through 6-phosphogluconate (MetaCyc:PWY-8004) [4 EXP annotations + InterPro:IPR004786]*\\n    |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate [0 direct annotations]\\n        |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde (MetaCyc:NPGLUCAT-PWY) [0 annotations]\\n        |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate (MetaCyc:PWY-2221) [0 annotations]\\n```\\n\\n* The 4 EXP annotations are to Thermoplasma Ta0809, Picrophilus PTO0332, and E.coli Eda by UniProt/EcoCyc\\n\\n\\nAs suggested in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29539, the 4 child terms should be merged into the parent \\\"Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\\" (GO:0061678), consistent with MetaCyc classing these as 'variant pathways' and the fact that such variants are better represented as GO-CAMs. Morever, the MetaCyc descriptions of the variants differ slightly (in their start/end points) from the GO descriptions.\\n\\nThe individual MetaCyc IDs should be made narrowMatch xrefs on the parent term GO:0061678.\\nAlso add a fourth variant, MetaCyc:ENTNER-DOUDOROFF-PWY, as narrowMatch xref.\\nAnd remove the 'MetaCyc:Entner-Doudoroff-Pathways' xref since that is the grouping class.\\n\\nIndividual GO term entries are shown below:\\n\\nid: GO:0061678\\nname: Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nnamespace: biological_process\\ndef: \\\"A cellular carbohydrate catabolic process that converts a carbohydrate to pyruvate and either glyceraldehyde or glyceraldehyde-3 phosphate by dehydration and aldol cleavage via a gluconate or 6-phosphogluconate intermediate.\\\" [GOC:dph, PMID:12921536]\\nxref: MetaCyc:Entner-Doudoroff-Pathways\\nis_a: GO:0016052 ! carbohydrate catabolic process\\nrelationship: has_pr... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAykORg\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n10:       \"body\": \"Also there is GO:0061688 glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway, 10 IEA annotations, no EXP. @sjm41 I think this too should be 'merged' into (obsolete with consider) GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway or GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Do you agree?\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-29T22:28:31Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4347989574\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n18:     },\n19:     {\n20:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2aYBQ\",\n21:       \"author\": {\n22:         \"login\": \"sjm41\"\n23:       },\n24:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n25:       \"body\": \"> Also there is GO:0061688 glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway, 10 IEA annotations, no EXP. @sjm41 I think this too should be 'merged' into (obsolete with consider) GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway or GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Do you agree?\\n\\n@raymond91125  Yes, I'd suggest that term is merged into its parent GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Thanks.\\n\\nI'll note that the 10 IEA annotations are all by CGD, based on evidence from [PomBase:SPAC4G9.12](https://www.pombase.org/gene/SPAC4G9.12) or [PomBase:SPBC660.16](https://www.pombase.org/gene/SPBC660.16).\\nLooking at those records in PomBase, they are annotated with a different BP \\\"pentose-phosphate shunt, oxidative branch (GO:0009051)\\\". So CGD may want to change those annotations anyway. (I don't know who the CGD contact is.)\",\n26:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T11:23:04Z\",\n27:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n28:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n29:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n30:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n31:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352022533\",\n32:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n33:     },\n34:     {\n35:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2pKsQ\",\n36:       \"author\": {\n37:         \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n38:       },\n39:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n40:       \"body\": \"CGD contact is @jlewsmith \\n\\nI assume that the IEA will get update automatically ? \",\n41:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T12:01:10Z\",\n42:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n43:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n44:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n45:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n46:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352264881\",\n47:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n48:     },\n49:     {\n50:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2ruNQ\",\n51:       \"author\": {\n52:         \"login\": \"sjm41\"\n53:       },\n54:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n55:       \"body\": \"> I assume that the IEA will get update automatically ?\\n\\nThat's what I thought, so I was surprised to see the mismatch between the current PomBase BP and the CGD annotations!\",\n56:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T12:07:34Z\",\n57:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n58:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n59:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n60:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n61:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352306741\",\n62:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n63:     },\n64:     {\n65:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2tkbA\",\n66:       \"author\": {\n67:         \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n68:       },\n69:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n70:       \"body\": \"I don't know how frequent CGD releases are.\",\n71:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T12:12:36Z\",\n72:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n73:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n74:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n75:       \"reactionGroups\": [\n76:         {\n77:           \"content\": \"THUMBS_UP\",\n78:           \"users\": {\n79:             \"totalCount\": 1\n80:           }\n81:         }\n82:       ],\n83:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352337004\",\n84:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n85:     },\n86:     {\n87:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABBKv3NQ\",\n88:       \"author\": {\n89:         \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n90:       },\n91:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n92:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please obsolete with replaced_by:\\nGO:0009255 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through 6-phosphogluconate -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061679 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061680 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061681 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061688 glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway -> GO:0006096 glycolytic process\",\n93:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-04T18:11:37Z\",\n94:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n95:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n96:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n97:       \"reactionGroups\": [\n98:         {\n99:           \"content\": \"EYES\",\n100:           \"users\": {\n101: 